  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Yes, you can minimize or block certain topics and keywords on Quora to reduce or eliminate content related to Trump (or any other topic) from your feed. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### **1. Mute Keywords or Topics**\n- **On Desktop**:  \n  1. Go to your **Feed Preferences**.  \n  2. Under **Muted Words**, add \"Trump\" or related keywords.  \n  3. You can also mute the **Politics** or **Donald Trump** topic entirely.  \n\n- **On Mobile**:  \n  1. Tap your profile picture and go to **Settings**.  \n  2. Navigate to **Feed Preferences** or **Content Preferences**.  \n  3. Add \"Trump\" or relevant topics to your muted list.  \n\n### **2. Hide Specific Questions or Answers**\n- If a Trump-related question pops up in your feed, you can hide it by clicking the three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022) next to the question and selecting **Hide**. This also helps Quora learn your preferences.  \n\n### **3. Adjust Your Followed Topics**\n- Unfollow topics like **Politics**, **U.S. Elections**, or **Donald Trump** if you\u2019re following them.  \n\n### **4. Report Low-Quality Content**\n- If you see repetitive or low-quality questions about Trump, you can report them to Quora moderators. This won\u2019t block the topic entirely but can improve your feed quality.  \n\nBy customizing your preferences, you can tailor your Quora experience to focus on topics that interest you the most.",
